# App host ‚Äî `infra/prod/docker-compose.app.yml` (RabbitMQ + messaging-service + nginx; no MinIO).
# Copy to **`.env`** in repo root (or `docker compose --env-file <path>`). **Never** commit a real **`.env`** (git ignores `.env`).
# Secrets: `RABBITMQ_PASS`, `JWT_SECRET`, `MONGODB_URI` (if it holds credentials), `AWS_*` ‚Äî see `docs/prod-secrets.md`.
# S3 detail: `docs/prod-s3-and-r2.md` (prod only; not the main README).
#
# Cross-host networking (PC-3, not README): `docs/prod-networking.md` ‚Äî default is routed L3 + `.env` URLs, optional shared Docker network on a single host.
# **Nginx (PC-4):** default mount `infra/prod/nginx/nginx.acme-http.conf` (HTTP + **/.well-known** for Certbot) + `certbot-www`. After `certonly`, switch to `infra/prod/nginx/nginx.https.conf` (TLS, **443**, `/etc/letsencrypt` ro ‚Äî see `docs/prod-acme-nginx.md` ¬ß(3)). Dev-style: `infra/dev/nginx/nginx.conf` and drop `certbot-www` if unneeded.
# **Certbot webroot:** `export CERTBOT_EMAIL=...` then `./infra/prod/scripts/certbot-webroot-ekko.sh`. Optional `CERTBOT_STAGING=1` for Let's Encrypt staging. **Do not** use `certbot --standalone` on :80.
# **Startup order:** (1) **Data** host: `docker compose -f infra/prod/docker-compose.data.yml up -d` (mongo, redis, minio reachable).
# (2) **App** host: set `MONGODB_URI`, `REDIS_URL`, `S3_*` in `.env`, then `docker compose -f infra/prod/docker-compose.app.yml up -d --build`
# and build `web-client` first. (3) Smoke: `https://ekko.biratbhattacharjee.com/v1/ready` (after TLS) or `http://localhost:8080/v1/ready` before TLS.
#
# **Before `docker compose -f infra/prod/docker-compose.app.yml up`:** build the web client so **`../../apps/web-client/dist`**
# exists and nginx can serve it:
#   cd apps/web-client && npm ci && npm run build
# Set `VITE_*` for that build (see below). Repeat **`npm run build`** on every static deploy, then restart nginx.
#
# --- Data host (PC-1) ‚Äî Mongo / Redis ---
# MONGODB_URI=mongodb://mongo.biratbhattacharjee.com:27017/messaging
# REDIS_URL=redis://<data-host>:6379
#
# --- S3-compatible API (MinIO on data host, or R2 / AWS) ---
# URL **messaging-service** uses **inside Docker** to reach MinIO (not the internal name `minio:9000` unless both stacks share one network):
# S3_ENDPOINT=http://<data-private-ip-or-dns>:9000
#
# Match **PC-1** MinIO root user (or R2 / AWS keys):
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=minio
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=minioadmin
#
# S3_BUCKET=messaging-media
# S3_REGION=us-east-1
#
# Base URL **browsers** use for presigned PUT / public object paths (must be reachable from user devices; not host.docker.internal):
# S3_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=http://<data-host-public-or-firewalled>:9000
# S3_ANONYMOUS_GET_OBJECT=true
# Optional: S3_PRESIGN_ENDPOINT=http://...  (if presign PUT must hit a different host than S3_PUBLIC_BASE_URL ‚Äî see messaging-service s3Client)
#
# App origin (emails, redirects):
# PUBLIC_APP_BASE_URL=https://ekko.biratbhattacharjee.com
#
# RABBITMQ_USER=messaging
# RABBITMQ_PASS=messaging
#
# --- Web client (build before `docker compose ... app`) ‚Äî see `apps/web-client/.env.example` (production block) ---
# `VITE_API_BASE_URL` = `https://ekko.biratbhattacharjee.com/v1` so `getSocketUrl()` ‚Üí `wss://ekko.biratbhattacharjee.com` (or `/v1` if SPA + API are same origin).
# cd apps/web-client
#   Copy the "Production / split stack" block from .env.example into .env.production.local, or one shot:
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://ekko.biratbhattacharjee.com/v1 npm run build
# VITE_S3_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=<same intent as S3_PUBLIC_BASE_URL for the browser>
# VITE_S3_BUCKET=messaging-media
# npm run build   (if you used .env.production.local with VITE_S3_* set)
